						<summary>

						<p>The inscription begins with a short Sanskrit version of the contents of the record. It registers an endowment of land for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mūlasthānam-Uḍaiyār by Muḍumbai Śōlaippirāṉ-Kramavittaṉ, a member of the <hi rend="italic">Āḷuṅgaṇaṁ</hi> of Pēriṅgūr, after purchasing the same from the assembly taxfree.</p>						

						</summary>
